  "description": [
    "2 Voice of Action Published each week by the Washington State Committee of Action the Fishermen and Cannery Workers Industrial Union the National Lumber Workers Union and the Unemployed Citizens League at 302 Maritime Bullding Seattle e e e e Editors Lowell Wakefield Alan Max et All news and advertising must be in by Thursday night Subscription rates 2 per year 1 for six months 60 cents for three e e Printed by Volunteer Union Labor THE POISON PRESS The press is conducting a monstrous cam paign of propaganda calculated to smash the longshoremens strike Each layoff each locking of a factory or lumber mill is laid at the door of the ILA How untrue the assertion is that curtailment is due to the longshoremens strike can be seen most clearly in the lumber industry The industry sick from the poisonous workings of the NRA already at a production level 60 per cent below 1928 and 1929 was due for another 17 per cent drop this month These facts were issuedi last week by the West Coast Lumbermens As sociation and their statement made no refer ence whatever to the longshormens strike as having anything to do with the situation"
